The paper discusses the evolution of nonmonotonic reasoning towards the computational paradigm of answer-set programming (ASP), which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) that deals with knowledge representation and reasoning. The paper also discusses the differentiation of ASP from classical logic programming, which falls under the subfield of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses research developments in ASP, which could fall under the subfields of programming languages (cs.PL), software engineering (cs.SE), and machine learning (cs.DL).
